h2 <a name="step1"></a> 1. Create a new CO2 data feed on Bayou-CO2

p.blurb Enter a name for your new feed, and you'll be provided with your new feed's <b>PUBLIC KEY</b> and <b>PRIVATE KEY</b>. Copy them down somewhere safe! (Read more about this <a href=""e>here</a>.)
form(action='/co2/manage' method='POST')
    fieldset
        h3 Create a New CO2 Data Feed
        label New Feed Name: 
        input#feed_name(type='text' name='feed_name' placeholder='Living room, Northwest side' required='')
        br
        br
        button(type='submit') Create new feed

<hr>  

h2 <a name="step2"></a> 2. Send CO2 data to your new feed

p.subheading <b>... via the browser (quick test):</b>

p.blurb You can send test CO2 data to your new feed by entering your feed's <b>PUBLIC KEY</b> and <b>PRIVATE KEY</b>:

form(action='/co2/manage' method='POST')
    fieldset
        h3 Send Test Data To Your CO2 Data Feed
        label Feed Public Key: 
        input#feed_name(type='text' name='feed_name' placeholder='Your Feed\'s PUBLIC KEY' required='')
        br
        label Feed Private Key: 
        input#feed_name(type='text' name='feed_name' placeholder='Your Feed\'s PRIVATE KEY' required='')
        br
        label Test CO2 Data: 
        input#feed_name(type='text' name='feed_name' placeholder='410' required='')
        br
        br
        button(type='submit') Send test data

p.subheading <b>... via your favorite hardware:</b>

p.blurb  A wide variety of microcontrollers, CO2 sensors, and programming frameworks can be used to send data to Bayou-CO2. You can read (or contribute to!) guidelines for doing this <a href="">here</a>. 

p.kit <img src="/images/compatibility.png">

p.subheading <b>... or via our hardware:</b>

p.blurb We have developed an <a href="https://edgecollective.io/posts/notes/co2/">Open Hardware CO2 monitoring kit</a>, based on the popular WiFi+Bluetooth <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ESP32">Espressif ESP32 microcontroller</a> and the <a href="https://www.sensirion.com/en/environmental-sensors/carbon-dioxide-sensors/carbon-dioxide-sensors-co2/">Sensiron SCD30 CO2 sensor</a>. The design files and assembly guides <a href="">are all available</a> (CERN Open Hardware License v2), or you can purchase one pre-assembled and pre-programmed to send data to Bayou-CO2.

p.kit <a href="https://edgecollective.io/posts/notes/co2/">Build or Purchase a PVOS CO2 Monitoring Kit</a>

p.kit <a href="https://edgecollective.io/posts/notes/co2/"><img src="/images/rev_e_built.png"></a>

<hr>  

h2 <a name="step3"></a>3. View your CO2 data

p.subheading <b>... via simple links:</b>

p.blurb You can retrieve CO2 data (as graphs, JSON, and CSV) using your feed's <b>PUBLIC KEY</b>.  They'll always be available (and free for you to share) at the following links:

pre
    code
        p <b>Feed Home:</b> http://data.pvos.org/co2/data/[PUBLIC KEY] <br>
        p <b>Feed as JSON:</b> http://data.pvos.org/co2/data/[PUBLIC KEY]/json <br>
        p <b>Feed as CSV:</b> http://data.pvos.org/co2/data/[PUBLIC KEY]/csv <br>
        //p <b>Feed graphs:</b> http://data.pvos.org/co2/data/[PUBLIC KEY]/graphs <br>

p.subheading <b>... or via a form:</b>

p.blurb Or, you can enter your <b>PUBLIC KEY</b> in the form below to go to its home page. At the feed's home page, you'll find links to graphs, JSON, and CSV for the feed data.

form(action='/co2/formData' method='POST')
    fieldset
        h3 View an Existing CO2 Data Feed
        label Feed Public Key: 
        input#feed_id_page(type='text' name='feed_id' placeholder='Your Feed\'s Public Key' required='')
        br
        br
        // <button type ="reset">Reset</button>
        button(type='submit') View Data

